{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Do we live in a borderless world?"},{"time":3000,"text":"Before you answer that, have a look at this map."},{"time":6000,"text":"Contemporary political map shows"},{"time":8000,"text":"that we have over 200 countries in the world today."},{"time":11000,"text":"That's probably more than at any time in centuries."},{"time":14000,"text":"Now, many of you will object."},{"time":16000,"text":"For you this would be a more appropriate map."},{"time":19000,"text":"You could call it TEDistan."},{"time":21000,"text":"In TEDistan, there are no borders,"},{"time":23000,"text":"just connected spaces and unconnected spaces."},{"time":26000,"text":"Most of you probably reside in one of the 40 dots"},{"time":30000,"text":"on this screen, of the many more"},{"time":32000,"text":"that represent 90 percent of the world economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35000,"text":"But let's talk about the 90 percent of the world population"},{"time":39000,"text":"that will never leave the place in which they were born."},{"time":42000,"text":"For them, nations, countries, boundaries, borders still matter a great deal,"},{"time":47000,"text":"and often violently."},{"time":50000,"text":"Now here at TED, we're solving some of the great"},{"time":52000,"text":"riddles of science and mysteries of the universe."},{"time":54000,"text":"Well here is a fundamental problem we have not solved:"},{"time":57000,"text":"our basic political geography."},{"time":59000,"text":"How do we distribute ourselves around the world?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":62000,"text":"Now this is important, because border conflicts"},{"time":65000,"text":"justify so much of the world's military-industrial complex."},{"time":68000,"text":"Border conflicts can derail"},{"time":70000,"text":"so much of the progress that we hope to achieve here."},{"time":73000,"text":"So I think we need a deeper understanding"},{"time":75000,"text":"of how people, money, power,"},{"time":77000,"text":"religion, culture, technology"},{"time":80000,"text":"interact to change the map of the world."},{"time":82000,"text":"And we can try to anticipate those changes,"},{"time":84000,"text":"and shape them in a more constructive direction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87000,"text":"So we're going to look at some maps of the past,"},{"time":89000,"text":"the present and some maps you haven't seen"},{"time":92000,"text":"in order to get a sense of where things are going."},{"time":95000,"text":"Let's start with the world of 1945."},{"time":98000,"text":"1945 there were just 100 countries in the world."},{"time":101000,"text":"After World War II, Europe was devastated,"},{"time":104000,"text":"but still held large overseas colonies:"},{"time":107000,"text":"French West Africa, British East Africa, South Asia, and so forth."},{"time":111000,"text":"Then over the late '40s,"},{"time":113000,"text":"'50s, '60s, '70s and '80s,"},{"time":115000,"text":"waves of decolonization took place."},{"time":117000,"text":"Over 50 new countries were born."},{"time":119000,"text":"You can see that Africa has been fragmented."},{"time":121000,"text":"India, Pakistan, Bangladesh, South East Asian nations created."},{"time":125000,"text":"Then came the end of the Cold War."},{"time":129000,"text":"The end of the Cold War and the disintegration of the Soviet Union."},{"time":132000,"text":"You had the creation of new states in Eastern Europe,"},{"time":135000,"text":"the former Yugoslav republics and the Balkans,"},{"time":137000,"text":"and the 'stans of central Asia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":140000,"text":"Today we have 200 countries in the world."},{"time":143000,"text":"The entire planet is covered"},{"time":145000,"text":"by sovereign, independent nation-states."},{"time":148000,"text":"Does that mean that someone's gain has to be someone else's loss?"},{"time":153000,"text":"Let's zoom in on one of the most strategic areas of the world,"},{"time":156000,"text":"Eastern Eurasia."},{"time":158000,"text":"As you can see on this map,"},{"time":160000,"text":"Russia is still the largest country in the world."},{"time":162000,"text":"And as you know, China is the most populous."},{"time":164000,"text":"And they share a lengthy land border."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166000,"text":"What you don't see on this map"},{"time":168000,"text":"is that most of Russia's 150 million people"},{"time":171000,"text":"are concentrated in its western provinces"},{"time":173000,"text":"and areas that are close to Europe."},{"time":175000,"text":"And only 30 million people are in its eastern areas."},{"time":179000,"text":"In fact, the World Bank predicts"},{"time":181000,"text":"that Russia's population is declining"},{"time":183000,"text":"towards about 120 million people"}]},{"cues":[{"time":186000,"text":"And there is another thing that you don't see on this map."},{"time":188000,"text":"Stalin, Khrushchev and other Soviet leaders"},{"time":191000,"text":"forced Russians out to the far east"},{"time":193000,"text":"to be in gulags, labor camps,"},{"time":195000,"text":"nuclear cities, whatever the case was."},{"time":198000,"text":"But as oil prices rose,"},{"time":200000,"text":"Russian governments have invested in infrastructure"},{"time":202000,"text":"to unite the country, east and west."},{"time":204000,"text":"But nothing has more perversely impacted"},{"time":207000,"text":"Russia's demographic distribution,"},{"time":209000,"text":"because the people in the east, who never wanted to be there anyway,"},{"time":212000,"text":"have gotten on those trains and roads"},{"time":214000,"text":"and gone back to the west."},{"time":216000,"text":"As a result, in the Russian far east today,"},{"time":219000,"text":"which is twice the size of India,"},{"time":221000,"text":"you have exactly six million Russians."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224000,"text":"So let's get a sense of what is happening in this part of the world."},{"time":227000,"text":"We can start with Mongolia, or as some call it, Mine-golia."},{"time":230000,"text":"Why do they call it that?"},{"time":232000,"text":"Because in Mine-golia, Chinese firms operate"},{"time":235000,"text":"and own most of the mines -- copper, zinc, gold --"},{"time":238000,"text":"and they truck the resources south and east into mainland China."},{"time":242000,"text":"China isn't conquering Mongolia."},{"time":244000,"text":"It's buying it."},{"time":247000,"text":"Colonies were once conquered. Today countries are bought."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250000,"text":"So let's apply this principle to Siberia."},{"time":254000,"text":"Siberia most of you probably think of"},{"time":256000,"text":"as a cold, desolate, unlivable place."},{"time":259000,"text":"But in fact, with global warming and rising temperatures,"},{"time":262000,"text":"all of a sudden you have vast wheat fields"},{"time":264000,"text":"and agribusiness, and grain being produced in Siberia."},{"time":268000,"text":"But who is it going to feed?"},{"time":270000,"text":"Well, just on the other side of the Amo River,"},{"time":273000,"text":"in the Heilongjiang and Harbin provinces of China,"},{"time":276000,"text":"you have over 100 million people."},{"time":278000,"text":"That's larger than the entire population of Russia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281000,"text":"Every single year, for at least a decade or more,"},{"time":284000,"text":"[60,000] of them have been voting with their feet,"},{"time":287000,"text":"crossing, moving north and inhabiting this desolate terrain."},{"time":292000,"text":"They set up their own bazaars and medical clinics."},{"time":294000,"text":"They've taken over the timber industry"},{"time":296000,"text":"and been shipping the lumber east, back into China."},{"time":299000,"text":"Again, like Mongolia,"},{"time":301000,"text":"China isn't conquering Russia. It's just leasing it."},{"time":305000,"text":"That's what I call globalization Chinese style."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309000,"text":"Now maybe this is what the map of the region"},{"time":311000,"text":"might look like in 10 to 20 years."},{"time":313000,"text":"But hold on. This map is 700 years old."},{"time":317000,"text":"This is the map of the Yuan Dynasty,"},{"time":319000,"text":"led by Kublai Khan, the grandson of Genghis Khan."},{"time":323000,"text":"So history doesn't necessarily repeat itself,"},{"time":325000,"text":"but it does rhyme."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327000,"text":"This is just to give you a taste of what's happening in this part of the world."},{"time":331000,"text":"Again, globalization Chinese style."},{"time":333000,"text":"Because globalization opens up all kinds of ways for us to"},{"time":336000,"text":"undermine and change the way we think about political geography."},{"time":341000,"text":"So, the history of East Asia in fact,"},{"time":344000,"text":"people don't think about nations and borders."},{"time":346000,"text":"They think more in terms of empires and hierarchies,"},{"time":349000,"text":"usually Chinese or Japanese."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351000,"text":"Well it's China's turn again."},{"time":353000,"text":"So let's look at how China is re-establishing"},{"time":355000,"text":"that hierarchy in the far East."},{"time":357000,"text":"It starts with the global hubs."},{"time":359000,"text":"Remember the 40 dots on the nighttime map"},{"time":362000,"text":"that show the hubs of the global economy?"},{"time":364000,"text":"East Asia today has more of those global hubs"},{"time":366000,"text":"than any other region in the world."},{"time":368000,"text":"Tokyo, Seoul, Beijing, Shanghai,"},{"time":371000,"text":"Hong Kong, Singapore and Sidney."},{"time":374000,"text":"These are the filters and funnels of global capital."},{"time":376000,"text":"Trillions of dollars a year are being brought into the region,"},{"time":379000,"text":"so much of it being invested into China."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382000,"text":"Then there is trade."},{"time":384000,"text":"These vectors and arrows represent ever stronger"},{"time":386000,"text":"trade relationships that China has"},{"time":388000,"text":"with every country in the region."},{"time":390000,"text":"Specifically, it targets Japan"},{"time":392000,"text":"and Korea and Australia,"},{"time":394000,"text":"countries that are strong allies of the United States."},{"time":396000,"text":"Australia, for example, is heavily dependent"},{"time":398000,"text":"on exporting iron ore and natural gas to China."},{"time":402000,"text":"For poorer countries, China reduces tariffs"},{"time":405000,"text":"so that Laos and Cambodia can sell their goods more cheaply"},{"time":408000,"text":"and become dependent on exporting to China as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411000,"text":"And now many of you have been reading in the news"},{"time":413000,"text":"how people are looking to China"},{"time":415000,"text":"to lead the rebound, the economic rebound, not just in Asia, but potentially for the world."},{"time":420000,"text":"The Asian free trade zone, almost free trade zone, that's emerging"},{"time":424000,"text":"now has a greater trade volume than trade across the Pacific."},{"time":428000,"text":"So China is becoming the anchor of the economy in the region."}]},{"cues":[{"time":431000,"text":"Another pillar of this strategy is diplomacy."},{"time":434000,"text":"China has signed military agreements with many countries in the region."},{"time":438000,"text":"It has become the hub of diplomatic institutions"},{"time":441000,"text":"such as the East Asian Community."},{"time":443000,"text":"Some of these organizations don't even have"},{"time":445000,"text":"the United States as a member."},{"time":447000,"text":"There is a treaty of nonaggression between countries,"},{"time":449000,"text":"such that if there were a conflict between China and the United States,"},{"time":453000,"text":"most countries vow to just sit it out,"},{"time":456000,"text":"including American allies like Korea and Australia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459000,"text":"Another pillar of the strategy,"},{"time":461000,"text":"like Russia, is demographic."},{"time":463000,"text":"China exports business people, nannies, students,"},{"time":466000,"text":"teachers to teach Chinese around the region,"},{"time":469000,"text":"to intermarry and to occupy ever greater"},{"time":472000,"text":"commanding heights of the economies."},{"time":474000,"text":"Already ethnic Chinese people"},{"time":476000,"text":"in Malaysia, Thailand and Indonesia"},{"time":479000,"text":"are the real key factors and drivers"},{"time":482000,"text":"in the economies there."},{"time":484000,"text":"Chinese pride is resurgent in the region"},{"time":486000,"text":"as a result."},{"time":488000,"text":"Singapore, for example, used to ban Chinese language education."},{"time":491000,"text":"Now it encourages it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":493000,"text":"If you add it all up what do you get?"},{"time":495000,"text":"Well, if you remember before World War II,"},{"time":497000,"text":"Japan had a vision"},{"time":499000,"text":"for a greater Japanese co-prosperity sphere."},{"time":502000,"text":"What's emerging today is what you might call"},{"time":504000,"text":"a greater Chinese co-prosperity sphere."},{"time":507000,"text":"So no matter what the lines on the map tell you"},{"time":509000,"text":"in terms of nations and borders,"},{"time":511000,"text":"what you really have emerging in the far east"},{"time":513000,"text":"are national cultures,"},{"time":515000,"text":"but in a much more fluid, imperial zone."},{"time":518000,"text":"All of this is happening without firing a shot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521000,"text":"That's most certainly not the case in the Middle East"},{"time":524000,"text":"where countries are still very uncomfortable"},{"time":527000,"text":"in the borders left behind by European colonialists."},{"time":530000,"text":"So what can we do to think about borders differently in this part of the world?"},{"time":534000,"text":"What lines on the map should we focus on?"},{"time":536000,"text":"What I want to present to you is what I call"},{"time":538000,"text":"state building, day by day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541000,"text":"Let's start with Iraq."},{"time":543000,"text":"Six years after the U.S. invasion of Iraq,"},{"time":545000,"text":"the country still exists more on a map than it does in reality."},{"time":548000,"text":"Oil used to be one of the forces holding Iraq together;"},{"time":551000,"text":"now it is the most significant cause of the country's disintegration."},{"time":555000,"text":"The reason is Kurdistan."},{"time":557000,"text":"The Kurds for 3,000 years"},{"time":559000,"text":"have been waging a struggle for independence,"},{"time":561000,"text":"and now is their chance to finally have it."},{"time":563000,"text":"These are pipeline routes, which emerge from Kurdistan,"},{"time":566000,"text":"which is an oil-rich region."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568000,"text":"And today, if you go to Kurdistan,"},{"time":570000,"text":"you'll see that Kurdish Peshmerga guerillas"},{"time":572000,"text":"are squaring off against the Sunni Iraqi army."},{"time":575000,"text":"But what are they guarding?"},{"time":577000,"text":"Is it really a border on the map?"},{"time":579000,"text":"No. It's the pipelines."},{"time":581000,"text":"If the Kurds can control their pipelines, they can set the terms"},{"time":583000,"text":"of their own statehood."},{"time":585000,"text":"Now should we be upset about this, about the potential disintegration of Iraq?"},{"time":588000,"text":"I don't believe we should."},{"time":590000,"text":"Iraq will still be the second largest oil producer in the world,"},{"time":593000,"text":"behind Saudi Arabia."},{"time":595000,"text":"And we'll have a chance to solve a 3,000 year old dispute."},{"time":598000,"text":"Now remember Kurdistan is landlocked."},{"time":600000,"text":"It has no choice but to behave."},{"time":602000,"text":"In order to profit from its oil"},{"time":604000,"text":"it has to export it through Turkey or Syria,"},{"time":607000,"text":"and other countries, and Iraq itself."},{"time":609000,"text":"And therefore it has to have amicable relations with them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612000,"text":"Now lets look at a perennial conflict in the region."},{"time":615000,"text":"That is, of course, in Palestine."},{"time":617000,"text":"Palestine is something of a cartographic anomaly"},{"time":621000,"text":"because it's two parts Palestinian, one part Israel."},{"time":624000,"text":"30 years of rose garden diplomacy"},{"time":626000,"text":"have not delivered us peace in this conflict."},{"time":629000,"text":"What might? I believe that what might"},{"time":632000,"text":"solve the problem is infrastructure."},{"time":634000,"text":"Today donors are spending billions of dollars on this."},{"time":637000,"text":"These two arrows are an arc,"},{"time":639000,"text":"an arc of commuter railroads and other infrastructure"},{"time":642000,"text":"that link the West Bank and Gaza."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645000,"text":"If Gaza can have a functioning port"},{"time":647000,"text":"and be linked to the West Bank, you can have a viable Palestinian state,"},{"time":650000,"text":"Palestinian economy."},{"time":652000,"text":"That, I believe, is going to bring peace to this particular conflict."},{"time":656000,"text":"The lesson from Kurdistan and from Palestine"},{"time":660000,"text":"is that independence alone, without infrastructure,"},{"time":663000,"text":"is futile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665000,"text":"Now what might this entire region look like"},{"time":667000,"text":"if in fact we focus on other lines on the map besides borders,"},{"time":671000,"text":"when the insecurities might abate?"},{"time":674000,"text":"The last time that was the case was actually"},{"time":676000,"text":"a century ago, during the Ottoman Empire."},{"time":678000,"text":"This is the Hejaz Railway."},{"time":680000,"text":"The Hejaz Railway ran from Istanbul to Medina via Damascus."},{"time":684000,"text":"It even had an offshoot running to Haifa"},{"time":686000,"text":"in what is today Israel, on the Mediterranean Sea."},{"time":688000,"text":"But today the Hejaz Railway lies in tatters, ruins."},{"time":692000,"text":"If we were to focus on reconstructing these curvy lines on the map,"},{"time":695000,"text":"infrastructure, that cross the straight lines, the borders,"},{"time":698000,"text":"I believe the Middle East would be a far more peaceful region."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702000,"text":"Now let's look at another part of the world,"},{"time":704000,"text":"the former Soviet Republics of Central Asia, the 'stans."},{"time":707000,"text":"These countries' borders originate from Stalin's decrees."},{"time":710000,"text":"He purposely did not want these countries to make sense."},{"time":714000,"text":"He wanted ethnicities to mingle"},{"time":716000,"text":"in ways that would allow him to divide and rule."},{"time":718000,"text":"Fortunately for them, most of their oil and gas resources"},{"time":721000,"text":"were discovered after the Soviet Union collapsed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":724000,"text":"Now I know some of you may be thinking, \"Oil, oil, oil."},{"time":727000,"text":"Why is it all he's talking about is oil?\""},{"time":729000,"text":"Well, there is a big difference in the way we used to talk about oil"},{"time":732000,"text":"and the way we're talking about it now."},{"time":734000,"text":"Before it was, how do we control their oil?"},{"time":737000,"text":"Now it's their oil for their own purposes."},{"time":739000,"text":"And I assure you it's every bit as important to them"},{"time":741000,"text":"as it might have been to colonizers and imperialists."},{"time":745000,"text":"Here are just some of the pipeline projections"},{"time":747000,"text":"and possibilities and scenarios"},{"time":749000,"text":"and routes that are being mapped out for the next several decades."},{"time":752000,"text":"A great deal of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754000,"text":"For a number of countries in this part of the world,"},{"time":756000,"text":"having pipelines is the ticket to becoming part of the global economy"},{"time":759000,"text":"and for having some meaning"},{"time":761000,"text":"besides the borders that they are not loyal to themselves."},{"time":763000,"text":"Just take Azerbaijan."},{"time":766000,"text":"Azerbaijan was a forgotten corner of the Caucuses,"},{"time":768000,"text":"but now with the Baku-Tbilisi-Ceyhan pipeline into Turkey,"},{"time":772000,"text":"it has rebranded itself as the frontier of the west."}]},{"cues":[{"time":776000,"text":"Then there is Turkmenistan, which most people think of"},{"time":779000,"text":"as a frozen basket case."},{"time":781000,"text":"But now it's contributing gas across the Caspian Sea"},{"time":784000,"text":"to provide for Europe,"},{"time":786000,"text":"and even a potentially Turkmen-"},{"time":788000,"text":"Afghan-Pakistan-India pipeline as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":792000,"text":"Then there is Kazakhstan, which didn't even have a name before."},{"time":794000,"text":"It was more considered South Siberia during the Soviet Union."},{"time":798000,"text":"Today most people recognize Kazakhstan"},{"time":800000,"text":"as an emerging geopolitical player. Why?"},{"time":802000,"text":"Because it has shrewdly designed pipelines to flow across the Caspian,"},{"time":806000,"text":"north through Russia, and even east to China."},{"time":810000,"text":"More pipelines means more silk roads, instead of the Great Game."},{"time":814000,"text":"The Great Game connotes dominance of one over the other."},{"time":818000,"text":"Silk road connotes independence and mutual trust."},{"time":821000,"text":"The more pipelines we have, the more silk roads we'll have,"},{"time":824000,"text":"and the less of a dominant Great Game competition"},{"time":827000,"text":"we'll have in the 21st century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":830000,"text":"Now let's look at the only part of the world that really has brought down its borders,"},{"time":833000,"text":"and how that has enhanced its strength."},{"time":835000,"text":"And that is, of course, Europe."},{"time":838000,"text":"The European Union began as just the coal and steel community of six countries,"},{"time":841000,"text":"and their main purpose was really to keep the rehabilitation of Germany"},{"time":845000,"text":"to happen in a peaceful way."},{"time":847000,"text":"But then eventually it grew into 12 countries,"},{"time":851000,"text":"and those are the 12 stars on the European flag."},{"time":853000,"text":"The E.U. also became a currency block,"},{"time":855000,"text":"and is now the most powerful trade block in the entire world."},{"time":859000,"text":"On average, the E.U. has grown by one country per year"},{"time":862000,"text":"since the end of the Cold War."},{"time":864000,"text":"In fact most of that happened on just one day."},{"time":867000,"text":"In 2004, 15 new countries joined the E.U."},{"time":869000,"text":"and now you have what most people consider"},{"time":872000,"text":"a zone of peace spanning 27 countries"},{"time":874000,"text":"and 450 million people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":877000,"text":"So what is next? What is the future of the European Union?"},{"time":881000,"text":"Well in light blue, you see the zones"},{"time":883000,"text":"or the regions that are at least two-thirds"},{"time":885000,"text":"or more dependent on the European Union"},{"time":887000,"text":"for trade and investment."},{"time":889000,"text":"What does that tell us? Trade and investment tell us"},{"time":891000,"text":"that Europe is putting its money where its mouth is."},{"time":895000,"text":"Even if these regions aren't part of the E.U.,"},{"time":897000,"text":"they are becoming part of its sphere of influence."},{"time":899000,"text":"Just take the Balkans. Croatia, Serbia"},{"time":902000,"text":"Bosnia, they're not members of the E.U. yet."},{"time":904000,"text":"But you can get on a German ICE train"},{"time":907000,"text":"and make it almost to Albania."},{"time":909000,"text":"In Bosnia you use the Euro currency already,"},{"time":912000,"text":"and that's the only currency they're probably ever going to have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":915000,"text":"So, looking at other parts of Europe's periphery, such as North Africa."},{"time":919000,"text":"On average, every year or two,"},{"time":921000,"text":"a new oil or gas pipeline opens up under the Mediterranean,"},{"time":924000,"text":"connecting North Africa to Europe."},{"time":927000,"text":"That not only helps Europe diminish its reliance"},{"time":929000,"text":"on Russia for energy,"},{"time":931000,"text":"but if you travel to North Africa today, you'll hear more and more people saying"},{"time":934000,"text":"that they don't really think of their region as the Middle East."},{"time":937000,"text":"So in other words, I believe that President Sarkozy of France"},{"time":940000,"text":"is right when he talks about a Mediterranean union."}]},{"cues":[{"time":944000,"text":"Now let's look at Turkey and the Caucasus."},{"time":947000,"text":"I mentioned Azerbaijan before."},{"time":949000,"text":"That corridor of Turkey and the Caucasus"},{"time":951000,"text":"has become the conduit for 20 percent"},{"time":953000,"text":"of Europe's energy supply."},{"time":955000,"text":"So does Turkey really have to be a member of the European Union?"},{"time":958000,"text":"I don't think it does. I think it's already part of"},{"time":960000,"text":"a Euro-Turkish superpower."}]},{"cues":[{"time":963000,"text":"So what's next? Where are we going to see borders change"},{"time":966000,"text":"and new countries born?"},{"time":968000,"text":"Well, South Central Asia, South West Asia"},{"time":970000,"text":"is a very good place to start."},{"time":972000,"text":"Eight years after the U.S. invaded Afghanistan"},{"time":974000,"text":"there is still a tremendous amount of instability."},{"time":976000,"text":"Pakistan and Afghanistan are still so fragile"},{"time":979000,"text":"that neither of them have dealt constructively"},{"time":981000,"text":"with the problem of Pashtun nationalism."},{"time":984000,"text":"This is the flag that flies in the minds"},{"time":986000,"text":"of 20 million Pashtuns"},{"time":988000,"text":"who live on both sides of the Afghan and Pakistan border."}]},{"cues":[{"time":991000,"text":"Let's not neglect the insurgency just to the south,"},{"time":994000,"text":"Balochistan. Two weeks ago,"},{"time":996000,"text":"Balochi rebels attacked a Pakistani military garrison,"},{"time":999000,"text":"and this was the flag that they raised over it."},{"time":1002000,"text":"The post-colonial entropy"},{"time":1004000,"text":"that is happening around the world is accelerating,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"and I expect more such changes to occur in the map"},{"time":1009000,"text":"as the states fragment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1011000,"text":"Of course, we can't forget Africa."},{"time":1013000,"text":"53 countries, and by far the most number"},{"time":1015000,"text":"of suspiciously straight lines on the map."},{"time":1018000,"text":"If we were to look at all of Africa"},{"time":1020000,"text":"we could most certainly acknowledge far more,"},{"time":1023000,"text":"tribal divisions and so forth."},{"time":1025000,"text":"But let's just look at Sudan, the second-largest country in Africa."},{"time":1029000,"text":"It has three ongoing civil wars,"},{"time":1031000,"text":"the genocide in Darfur, which you all know about,"},{"time":1034000,"text":"the civil war in the east of the country,"},{"time":1036000,"text":"and south Sudan."},{"time":1038000,"text":"South Sudan is going to be having a referendum in 2011"},{"time":1041000,"text":"in which it is very likely to vote itself independence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1044000,"text":"Now let's go up to the Arctic Circle."},{"time":1048000,"text":"There is a great race on for energy resources"},{"time":1050000,"text":"under the Arctic seabed."},{"time":1052000,"text":"Who will win? Canada? Russia? The United States?"},{"time":1054000,"text":"Actually Greenland."},{"time":1056000,"text":"Several weeks ago Greenland's [60,000] people"},{"time":1059000,"text":"voted themselves self-governance rights"},{"time":1061000,"text":"from Denmark."},{"time":1063000,"text":"So Denmark is about to get a whole lot smaller."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1066000,"text":"What is the lesson from all of this?"},{"time":1068000,"text":"Geopolitics is a very unsentimental discipline."},{"time":1072000,"text":"It's constantly morphing and changing the world,"},{"time":1074000,"text":"like climate change."},{"time":1076000,"text":"And like our relationship with the ecosystem"},{"time":1078000,"text":"we're always searching for equilibrium"},{"time":1080000,"text":"in how we divide ourselves across the planet."},{"time":1083000,"text":"Now we fear changes on the map."},{"time":1085000,"text":"We fear civil wars, death tolls,"},{"time":1087000,"text":"having to learn the names of new countries."},{"time":1090000,"text":"But I believe that the inertia of the existing borders that we have today"},{"time":1093000,"text":"is far worse and far more violent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1095000,"text":"The question is how do we change those borders,"},{"time":1097000,"text":"and what lines do we focus on?"},{"time":1099000,"text":"I believe we focus on the lines that cross borders,"},{"time":1101000,"text":"the infrastructure lines."},{"time":1103000,"text":"Then we'll wind up with the world we want, a borderless one."},{"time":1106000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1108000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}